According to the operator, the airplane was parked at the gate preparing to be pushed back 
when the damage occurred. A ground crew worker had connected an air-starter cart to the 
airplane, and then determined that the air cart was not functioning properly. The worker 
attempted to pull the cart away from the airplane without disconnecting the hose, resulting in 
substantial damage to the skin panels on the left, lower side of the airplane's fuselage.
